OL,3,CThieves trash hospice counselling
OL,4,Crooms in early hours raid
OL,6,FThe thieves made off with computers, a
OL,7,Flarge screen television, a kettle and
OL,8,Fbottles of alcohol.
OL,10,FNurses working the night shift spotted
OL,11,Fthe criminals on CCTV and called
OL,12,Fpolice. They then stood beside
OL,13,Fpatients' beds to offer protection
OL,14,Funtil officers arrived.
OL,16,FHospice chief executive Tracey
OL,17,FWilcocks said: "We are all in absolute
OL,18,Fshock. We know times are tough, but to
OL,19,Fknowingly break into and steal from a
OL,20,Fhospice is beyond belief.
